#Text=1. Introduction
#Text=Free radical nitric oxide ( NO ) is generated via non-enzymatic and enzymatic pathways in plants .
#Text=As a multifunctional physiological regulator , NO has been shown to be involved in every aspect of plant growth and every developmental process in plants .
#Text=Furthermore , an increasing body of evidence has indicated that NO could play an essential role in response to various abiotic stresses .
#Text=Previous studies suggested that NO could exert its effects depending on the cyclic guanosine monophosphate ( cGMP ) signaling pathway .
#Text=For example , NO could promote the adventitious rooting of marigold through the cGMP-dependent pathway .
#Text=Additionally , the emerging picture is that NO also could operate biological functions through protein S -nitrosylation which is a NO-dependent posttranslational modification ( PTM ) .
#Text=It has been shown that NO groups could be covalently bound to cysteine ( Cys ) residues of target proteins , resulting in the formation of S -nitrosothiols during S -nitrosylation .
#Text=At present , increasing evidence demonstrates that S -nitrosylation might be involved in processes for regulating the growth , development , and stress responses in plants .
#Text=In general , proteomics deals with the large-scale determination of gene and cellular function directly at the protein level .
#Text=Recently , global protein S -nitrosylation has been identified using the proteomic approach .
#Text=According to Hu et al. , more than 2200 S -nitrosylated proteins have been identified in mammals and plants .
#Text=In the present work , several S -nitrosylated proteins have been identified using proteomic analyses in different plants .

#Text=For example , Lindermayr et al. identified proteins , which , when treated with NO , were involved in various pathways such as cytoskeleton organization , metabolic processes , redox homeostasis , as well as cellular signaling transduction .
#Text=Moreover , Morisse et al. identified 492 S -nitrosylated proteins and 392 sites in chlamydomonas reinhardtii cells , which were treated with S -nitrosoglutathione ( GSNO ) .
#Text=Moreover , 926 proteins that undergo nitrosylation have been identified in Arabidopsis .
#Text=Certain NO target proteins have been pointed out as important for regulating physiological and pathological cellular processes through proteomic and transcriptomic analyses .
#Text=Although the identification research on S -nitrosylation is increasing , the mechanism of S -nitrosylation during root development remains unclear .
#Text=The aim of this study was to identify possible candidates for S -nitrosylation during adventitious rooting to reveal the biological function of NO at the protein level in plants .
#Text=Therefore , we conducted this experiment to detect and identify the S -nitrosylated proteins during NO-induced adventitious rooting in cucumber explants .

#Text=The objective of this study was to decipher the novel role of protein S -nitrosylation in the process of adventitious root development in order to further improve our understanding of NO signaling transduction in molecular mechanisms .
